  <script type="text/javascript">
   function bookmarksite(title, url) {
            if (window.sidebar && window.sidebar.addPanel) // firefox
                window.sidebar.addPanel(title, url, "");
            else if (window.opera && window.print) { // opera
                var elem = document.createElement('a');
                elem.setAttribute('href', url);
                elem.setAttribute('title', title);
                elem.setAttribute('rel', 'sidebar');
                elem.click();
            }
            else if (window.external && ('AddFavorite' in window.external))// ie
                window.external.AddFavorite(url, title);
        }
        function DoSearch() {
            var searchtext = $find('ctl00_txtRegularSearch').get_value();
            location.href = "/Search/" + replacestring(searchtext);
            return false;
        }
        function replacestring(stringtoreplace) {
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split("&").join("$A$");

            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split('*').join("$ST$");
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split("'").join("$SQ$");
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split('"').join("$DQ$");
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split("/").join("$FS$");
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split("\\").join("$BS$");
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split(",").join("$C$");
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split(";").join("$SC$");
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split("(").join("$LB$");
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split(")").join("$RB$");
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split("{").join("$LCB$");
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split("}").join("$RCB$");
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split(":").join("$CO$");
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split("#").join("$HA$");
            stringtoreplace = stringtoreplace.split("+").join("$PL$");

            return stringtoreplace
        }

        function forceLoginout(eventTarget, eventArgument) {
            if (!theForm.onsubmit || (theForm.onsubmit() != false)) {
                theForm.action = "/MyAccount";
            }
        }
  </script>

              <span id="MainContent_lblLawByTerritory">
               <div style="width: 98%;">
                <p>
                 Australia's ten Territories are home to over half a million Australians. Each territory has different legal origins, and a different relationship with the Australian Government. Choose the territory you are interested in for details of its laws and governance:
                </p>
                <table style="width: 100%;">
                 <tbody>
                  <tr bgcolor="#ececec">
                   <td valign="top">
                    <a href="/content/NSGT1/#Ashmore">
                     Ashmore and Cartier Islands
                    </a>
                   </td>
                   <td valign="top">
                    <a href="/content/NSGT1/#Coral">
                     Coral Sea Islands
                    </a>
                   </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                   <td valign="top">
                    <a href="/content/NSGT2/#Antarctic">
                     Australian Antarctic Territory
                    </a>
                   </td>
                   <td valign="top">
                    <a href="/content/NSGT2/#Heard">
                     Heard and McDonald Islands
                    </a>
                   </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr bgcolor="#ececec">
                   <td valign="top">
                    <a href="/content/SGTerritories/#ACT">
                     Australian Capital Territory (ACT)
                    </a>
                   </td>
                   <td valign="top">
                    <a href="/content/NSGT1/#Jervis">
                     Jervis Bay Territory
                    </a>
                   </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                   <td valign="top">
                    <a href="/content/NSGT1/#Christmas">
                     Christmas Island*
                    </a>
                   </td>
                   <td valign="top">
                    <a href="/content/SGTerritories/#Norfolk">
                     Norfolk Island
                    </a>
                   </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr bgcolor="#ececec">
                   <td valign="top">
                    <a href="/content/NSGT1/#Cocos">
                     Cocos (Keeling) Islands*
                    </a>
                   </td>
                   <td valign="top">
                    <a href="/content/SGTerritories/#NT">
                     Northern Territory (NT)
                    </a>
                   </td>
                  </tr>
                 </tbody>
                </table>
                <p>
                 In the past, the Australian Government has also administered territory in Nauru, New Guinea and Papua. These territories have since become the independent nations of Nauru and of Papua New Guinea.
                </p>
                <p>
                 For more information about how Australia acquired its external territories - that is, all territories except the ACT, the NT and Jervis Bay Territory - please see Alan Kerr's book
                 <a href="http://www.regional.gov.au/territories/publications/index.aspx" target="_blank">
                  A Federation In These Seas
                 </a>
                 <img alt="This link will take you away from the Federal Register" src="/Images/Leaving.gif" style="border: currentColor; border-image: none;"/>
                 .
                </p>
                <p>
                 <span style="font-size: smaller;">
                  *these two territories are jointly administered and are also known as the Indian Ocean Territories (IOTs)
                 </span>
                </p>

                <p>
